<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> clarks summit, pennsylvania 4/14/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.94)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10268'>steven "GIMLItheTANK" colby</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=10268&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 14, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> I just put a deck together this past monday. It was a shoulder fire light side with sauron orcs and all their nasty events and conditions. I played tested wednesday against a few players at mazz&#39;z card shop in clark summit. The big guy i played was Pat Ziagos (1700 rating- 187th in the world). It faired really well aginst him actually i didnt take a loss that whole night. Then i played with it again on april 13th the day before the tournament against Pat again and TD MArtin (who was running the tournament on the 14th). Pat this time made major changes and faired alot better but i still won in the end. It was a good game and Pat made some very good strategic moves but shoulder fire is just too darn effective. I knew if i played with it in the tournament Pat would change his deck to beat me and i was a little worried and even considered changing my whole deck but instead i only changed one thing ( i added gimli son of gloin for i thought he was goin to put in some goblins that got rid of dwarf allies and basically putting an end to my shoulder fire engine). <br>
The day of the tournament was beautiful. Absolutely gorgeous outside. Me and my girlfreind (teh beautiful stefanie simon) get to Mazz&#39;s around 12:30 ran a little late. Usually there is between 14-20 lord of the rings players, some coming as far away as New York to play. But that was not the case, we get a turn out of eight players. Not as many as i hoped or anybody hope dbut still enough to have a good time. Mazz Card tournaments are always alot of fun. At least there was not goin to be any byes.<br>
The first round pairings go up and by luck of the draw i have to play my girlfriend in the first round.<br>
<br>
First round<br>
Me (stevn colby 1620)shoulder fire/sauron orcs<br>
 vs Stefanie Simon (1533) NINE WALKERS/cave troll-moria<br>
me and stefanie we play alot against each other. I actually built her deck where the concepts are easy to understand. There is alot of companions with adders to take as much damage as possible and on her shadow she has 4 big trolls to try and wipe the floor up with any unsuspecting player.<br>
Bid-i bid 3 and she bids 3 (just like i told her) i get the high roll and decide togo first.<br>
My starting fellowship is arwen and rare legolas. The engine gets started early, in my opening hand i draw a aragorn kie with his bow, shoulder to shoulder and two dwarf companions. I drop everything and give her a whole lot of twilight. She doenst drop too much a couple things but my archers pick her off. I double move and heal at the sanctuary. Nothing exciting happening on my shadow except by the time she gets to site 4 i have 4 bowmen out and two utwe&#39;s. The pain is hurting. Shes basically down to on emove a turn. I move past site 4 without much trouble. Site five i face up against the rare balrog who eats boromir, lord of dying spectacularly. I move again to site six since the balrog will be discarded. The shadow there is alot of morgul hunters flying down hating away her poor defensless aragorn and sneaking up and biting gimli in the butt with enduring evils. She ges to site six by the end of the game. Now back to the good guys. I move to her site 7 the one where there is no archery. She drops a key ward with a cave troll. I cant do anything but brace for impact but there i shope i have a little fodder left (gimli and sam). Aragorn takes on the keyward beating the snot out o fhim for bringing the scourge out. The troll eats gimli then picks his bones out with sam. I stop. My next turn i move and she drops another cave troll. BUt this time i use my engine and shoulder fire the troll to death. BUt now my guys are feeling the heat, time is running down and aragorn and legolas are close to death. So i take a chance and move. SHe first drops a scout for free with a scimitar. She says she doesnt have the troll in here hand but with the draw she gets it and drops the bad boy. She then uses the sites special ability to draw cards for burdens. She drops like five more little guys. Im a little worried so i use aragorn and legolas to pick off the smaller guys and let the troll eat aragorn and legolas. <br>
Full Win- 3 points<br>
<br>
Highs-surviving three trolls in a row.<br>
Lows-having to play and beat my girlfriend:(<br>
<br>
round two<br>
Me vs<br>
Adam Goldstein(1630)-aragorn/gimli pumpers/moria<br>
we had to play this one fast because adam had to go out in a little bit. I bid three and he bids three we roll a six sided die and win. I go first, play the pony pull aragorn. stop at site 2 because he had a lot of pool an dhad decided not to play anything. Kinda scary situation. He goes he plays a bunch of stuff. so i drop a orc bowmen and a utwe. Allowing the scout to die fruitlessly to archery. He moves to site three-- bad mistake i still had pool left (alot). I get a morgul hunter and a enduring evil. He puts aragorn up against the hunter. I drop the enduinrg evil and overwhelm aragorn. Now half his good guy cards are useless. Hes very frustrated. I move only one site form now on. Because the pain was too much for him. I have out three orc bowmens, two utwes, and frodo is thinned and strecthed. When he hits site five arwen takes a hate bullet. Site seven gimli take sthe other hate bullet and legolas takes bowmen shots. All that left is a exhausted frodo,and i just get my engine up to maximum power. He concedes (his only loss of the day).<br>
Full Win 6 points<br>
<br>
highs-that my sauron orcs were being bad hiney mofia hit men with their drive bys and their pressure(the first time i ever killed frodo)i always get site nine wins.<br>
Lows-none really, only that if he had not doubled moved to site three it would of been a different closer game.Oh yeah we played this game in fifteen minutes talking about speed.<br>
<br>
Round three<br>
Me vs<br>
Martin the TD of the day (1560) <br>
Dwarf and Gandalf spells /urukhai<br>
This was a game i was a little worried about. I thought he would put spies in from playing me the night before but he didnt, possibly the game difference (but still a very close and great game). I bid two and win chose togo first with the pony. I play alot of stuff to build up my engine giving martin a whopping 18 pool to work with. :)I move to site 2 and he drops some 3 big bad urukhai. I handle them pretty good i only took six wounds and didnt lose a character. I stop. Martin then goes, i have nothing of value in my minion side. He gets a free double move to site 3. I go an dmove to site three and stay because i need to heal. I was worried martin was going to win the race. But i get some luck and drop a big bad morgul hunter with a bowmen at site 4. He stops. I move to site 4 he plays nothing so i go for the gusto and go to site five. Where he drops four big urukhai. They kill boromir and sam. Im ok now though because the shoulder engine is now at full power and i can now pick off any urukahi at will barring spies of saruman.He moves and stays at site five because i had just dropped some big bad mean hunters. This is where it gets hectic. I move to site six. Shoulder fire away his minions. Instead of staying i double move to site seven.Its the no archery phase, i heal up my two archers and arwen, a major cog in the machine gets ravaged by a urukhai. Martin goes he meets little resistance at site 6 and stays! He needed to move again to have a chance at winning. This is what helped me win. Instead of the deadly double move i was expecting on my turn i instead take a sfe single move and stay. I dont play any minions (times running out)he double moves to site 8 and has to stay. I walk into site nine and win.Great game.<br>
full win-9 points<br>
Highs-making the right choice in skipping over site 6 to get the site nine win.<br>
Lows-Getting into a position where i have to skip over a sanctuary to win. (good game martin, nice strategy)<br>
Suggestion-if martin pushes to site seven, thsi would force me to double move for the site 9 win because my minions were not doing anything, and he kept sleeping away my conditions, so he could of doubled moved the next turn if i stayed at site 8. A double move on part would prolly of meant Martin killing everyone.:)whew!<br>
<br>
Round 4 only 2 undeafeteds left<br>
Me vs (dun dun dun)<br>
Pat Ziagos (1710)Ranger choke/moria, the man that had his decked metaed for mine. I was nervous i am hoping my counter strike to his meta would be enough. This is the game basically to decide the tourney.<br>
I bid three and go first. I start seeing his changes early as he begins discarded my main component to my shoulder engine (dwarf allies). I get to site three but at the cost of grimir and thrarin. Ranger choke is very effective. It clogged my hand with the expensive roaming and conditions that are known of sauron culture. Im not doing too much to him minion wise, justenough to slow him down. I draw a gimli and my engine is up and running and then when i hit site 4 or 5 i find out his next big change its a troll with its chain. SO i cant shoot the troll down or else lose my archers(good move Pat). I let the troll give boromir two wounds and aragorn two. I stay. Nothing major happening shadow, so lets go to my turn. I move to site sicx stay and heal. He moves to five stays. NOw here is where the game is won and lost. I hadnt grabbed my thror&#39;s map all game so im moving to his site 7. I thought it was going to be the game ending site seven-discard all allies. I would of been out of arrows. BUtits the no archery phase one again. WHEW!!! My guys take a few wounds nothing major. He moves to site 6 and stays to heal. I move to eight. He drops a troll a few orcs and enquea- i have six companions out. Its time for some of his aimed archery. Maneuver phase he makes a mistake instead of taking out rare boro he tries to kill gimli which i heal with shoulder to shoulder. That was his only mistake of the game. Boromir takes on the troll both times and dies. the rest i handle easily. If enquea had taken out boromir two companions would of died to the troll instead of one. That means next turn i would of had three companions---frodo,aragorn, and legolas. Instead i had five arwen, gimli, frodo, aragorn, and legolas. Time is running out so i let pat double move to eight, i dont play anything because i need the time. My turn begins and i have one minute left. SO this is going to be a full win one way or the other. I move and he drops a boat load of cheap no costing orcs with their tank the troll. I kill off the swarm with my archery and let the troll kill aragorn and arwen. SIte nine win.BEST GAME OF THE TOURNAMENT. pat is a great player and this game should of been his if he had killed boromir.thats the last time i let him see my deck before a tournament. LOL just kidding<br>
full win-12 points<br>
<br>
highs-my counter to his counter worked. getting lucky by beating pat.<br>
lows-there was none. other than the boromir affair this game was played beautiuflly.<br>
<br>
round five<br>
im all alone at the top. if i win i win the tourney. Lose a final confrontation with pat.<br>
me vs<br>
Mark mattingly(1500) hobbit/sauron<br>
New player but played really well. I bid three and he bids four, he goes first.He double moves and has teh lea dthe whole game, he slowed me down and even hated away my legolas. Basically its a see saw battle between minions. Hes at site five with two hobbits, aragorn, and boromir. I drop a tower assassin he blocks with boromir and i overwhelme the rare boromir by dropping two enbduring evils. He loses the game here when he double moves to site six and i drop two more minions (orc inquisitor and orc scout). I use the orc inquisitor and his stealth gets discarded. This allows for frodo to be overwhelmed. A good game.<br>
Full win-15 points<br>
<br>
Highs-overwhelming frodo at site six.<br>
Lows-nbeing so far behind in the race.<br>
<br>
I won the tournament. Ive won two tournaments now out of five.<br>
<br>
Heres how the field broke down-<br>
1st-steven colby-15 points-prize rare foil in the mail and a 24 dollar gift certificate (the larger the playing field the bigger the gift certificate--if 20 play 60 dollar giftcertificiate)<br>
2nd-Pat Ziagos-13 points-14 dollar gift certificate and uncommon foil.<br>
3rd-Adam Goldstein-12 points-participation award<br>
4th-Mark Mattingly-8 points-common foil<br>
5th-Stefanie Simon-8 points-a pack<br>
6th through eight i didnt get a chance to get their names but they all got foils.<br>
I use my gift certificate and buy 8 packs. Heres the goodies i got-<br>
double shot, Lurtz&#39;s battle cry, FOIL a servant to the secret fire(rare, and its cool looking), Aragorn ranger of the north, Gandlaf friend of shire folk, orc bowmen, the gaffer, valiant man of the west foil. avery nice selection.<br>
<br>
Tournament props- go to td&#39;s pat and martin who ran a fun tournament. The prizes were great and the atmosphere friendly. Also to the owner mazz for allowing us to have these tourneys at his establishment,<br>
